  "source_notes": "\"Constellations '77\" quotes Kraum, from him.  Notable Nativities No.083 gave 1868, which Leo corrected in Modern Astrology 7/1928, writing that, \"Cheiro himself gave 1866.\"  The location given was Dublin.\\nPatrick Mahoney, a personal friend of Cheiro, gave 1862 in \"Escape Into the Psychic Kingdom.\" Jon St. Germain gives the location of Bray, just south of Dublin.\\nSy Scholfield notes that \"William John Warner\" with a birth date of \"1 Nov 1866\" in \"Bray, County Wicklow, Ireland\" is listed in the UK and Ireland Find A Grave Index. The same name, date and year is listed in the \"Ireland, Select Births and Baptisms, 1620-1911\" index on ''Ancestry.com''. The Ireland Civil Registration Births Index on the same website lists William John Warner (name), 1866 (Date of Registration) and Rathdown (Registration District). Time of death given by a nurse attending his death is quoted in ''Los Angeles Evening Citizen News'' (Hollywood, California), 9 Oct 1936, page 1.\\n",
